# Cargo build output.
/target/

# Cargo lockfile — keep for binaries, omit for libraries by convention.
# We keep it because the perf budgets are wall-clock tests and dep version
# drift would invalidate the headroom assumptions. Drop this line if/when
# the crate is widely re-used as a library and the lockfile becomes noise.

# Insta pending snapshots — these are intermediate review artifacts, not
# committed. Once a contributor accepts a snapshot with `cargo insta review`,
# the resulting `.snap` file IS committed but the `.new` siblings are not.
*.snap.new
*.pending-snap

# IDE / editor scratch.
.idea/
.vscode/
*.swp
*.swo
.DS_Store
